    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/proportion-of-trains-running-on-time"/>
    <title>Proportion of trains running on time</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;h2 id="dft-business-plan-input-indicator"&gt;DfT Business Plan input indicator&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id="geographical-coverage-dft-franchised-train-operators-great-britain"&gt;Geographical coverage: DfT franchised train operators (Great Britain)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3 id="information-broken-down-by-train-operator"&gt;Information broken down by: Train operator&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h2 id="latest-data"&gt;Latest data&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;88.9 per cent of trains arrived on time between 14 October 2012 and 10 November 2012 in Great Britain, a slight decrease from 89.3 per cent for the same period last year (GB total). The GB average headline figure incorporates Public Performance Measure (&lt;abbr title="Public Performance Measure"&gt;PPM&lt;/abbr&gt;) averages for operators franchised by devolved administrations (Arriva Trains Wales, First Scotrail, London Overground and Merseyrail), and non-franchised operators (Grand Central, Heathrow Express and Hull Trains), however, the following table covers only DfT franchised operators.&lt;/p&gt;

