&lt;p&gt;For the second year running, in 2011/12 First Capital Connect was the only train operator with a negative subsidy per passenger mile, meaning that it paid government a larger premium than the effective subsidy it received via the Network Grant payment to Network Rail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Northern Rail received the highest subsidy per passenger mile of 34.9 pence per mile in 2011/12.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Subsidy per passenger mile CSV file contains a more detailed breakdown of the subsidy figures for each train operator:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="background-information"&gt;Background information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This indicator provides information about the amount of subsidy paid to Train Operating Companies, both directly by the Department for Transport and indirectly via grants to Network Rail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no recognised rule for allocating the network grant across franchises. The distribution of fixed track access charges has been used to allocate the network grant by train operator.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;publishing schedule: annual&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;last updated: 8 October 2012&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;next update: August 2013&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Further information about this indicator can be found in the measurement template.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="other-related-data-and-information"&gt;Other related data and information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.rail-reg.gov.uk/upload/xls/govt-support-to-rail-industry-by-toc-table.xls"&gt;Subsidy data published by the Office of Rail Regulation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Network Grant estimates derived from DfT internal management information are apportioned between train operators in proportion to fixed track charges. The fixed track charges schedule is available on the Office of Rail Regulation’s website at &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.rail-reg.gov.uk/upload/pdf/cp4-pl-fixed_track_charges_sched_181208.pdf"&gt;www.rail-reg.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="further-information"&gt;Further information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you would like further information on this indicator, please contact DfT’s Rail Statistics team at: &lt;a href="mailto:rail.stats@dft.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;rail.stats@dft.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
